            <fr:route>/schm-OSC4/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Characterisation of universally closed maps between schemes">Characterisation of universally closed maps between schemes</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  The following are equivalent for a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> between <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link>:
  <html:ol><html:li> It is a <fr:link href="/schm-2LXR/" title="Closed and universally closed maps of schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-2LXR/" display-uri="schm-2LXR" type="local">universally closed map between schemes</fr:link>. </html:li>
    <html:li> It is a <fr:link href="/topl-BC42/" title="Characterisation of universally closed maps between topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-BC42/" display-uri="topl-BC42" type="local">universally closed map between topological spaces</fr:link>. </html:li>
    <html:li> It is <fr:link href="/schm-2LXR/" title="Closed and universally closed maps of schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-2LXR/" display-uri="schm-2LXR" type="local">closed</fr:link>, and for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex> the fibre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(y)]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. </html:li>
    <html:li> It is <fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="/idem-comm-SQ5X/" title="P-maps and q-maps" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-SQ5X/" display-uri="idem-comm-SQ5X" type="local">q-map</fr:link>. </html:li></html:ol></html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    The equivalence (2) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Leftrightarrow ]]></fr:tex> (3) is from <fr:link href="/topl-BC42/" title="Characterisation of universally closed maps between topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-BC42/" display-uri="topl-BC42" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-BC42/" display-uri="topl-BC42" /></fr:link>. (2) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> (1) is evident.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    To show (1) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> (3), suppose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a universally closed map between schemes. For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex>, since pullback of schemes are topological (cf. <fr:link href="/schm-S9SD/" title="Fibre products of schemes are topological" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-S9SD/" display-uri="schm-S9SD" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-S9SD/" display-uri="schm-S9SD" /></fr:link>), it follows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(y) \to  1]]></fr:tex> must also be a universally closed map of schemes. By <fr:link href="/topl-KVQM/" title="A characterisation of compact topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-KVQM/" display-uri="topl-KVQM" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-KVQM/" display-uri="topl-KVQM" /></fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(y)]]></fr:tex> must be quasi-compact.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    For (2) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> (4), by a similar proof of <fr:link href="/topl-KVQM/" title="A characterisation of compact topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-KVQM/" display-uri="topl-KVQM" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-KVQM/" display-uri="topl-KVQM" /></fr:link> one can show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> must be quasi-compact. It is a q-map because it is closed.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    To show (4) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Rightarrow ]]></fr:tex> (1), it suffices to observe that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact and a q-map, then by <fr:link href="/schm-9N69/" title="Quasi-compact closed maps between schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-9N69/" display-uri="schm-9N69" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-9N69/" display-uri="schm-9N69" /></fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> must be closed; furthermore, both quasi-compactness (<fr:link href="/schm-5YJS/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5YJS/" display-uri="schm-5YJS" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5YJS/" display-uri="schm-5YJS" /></fr:link>) and q-maps (<fr:link href="/idem-comm-UF37/" title="Closure properties of p-maps and q-maps" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-UF37/" display-uri="idem-comm-UF37" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-UF37/" display-uri="idem-comm-UF37" /></fr:link>) are closed under pullbacks, thus such maps are universally closed.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
